originalText.text:
some years back i tried to take a picture of the one world trade center from the public sidewalk next to this business at 12:00 midnight and some guard with a minute from this business jogged over and told me to "get off their property with that tripod"

i was surprised and angered by the response but did as he said respectfully and promptly.  maybe im wrong but last i check a public side walk is city property! not private property.  so i had to walk across the street, way down to get out of the way of the street lights to get the shot.

So obliviously i was a tourist just wanting some night shots of the trade center.  the sidewalks were quiet and it would have only taken me 5 minutes to get the angle and lighting i wanted but they sure were quick to shoo me away.  i get that the guard was just doing his job  but if this is what the business is like to people on "their private sidewalks" i would never do businesses with them if i lived there.  it doesn't look like anyone likes them by the look of the other reviews. and im not the first to complain about this surprisingly.

My conclusion,  i got a taste of how bad this place is.  Extremely disgraceful business!
